Neuropodia well-developed, conical mounds. Compound neurochaetae, with heterogomph shafts and fine bidentate falcigerous blades (
Fig. 2D
). Neurochaetal count, mid-body segments, at least 20–26 (chaetae densely packed and difficult to accurately count). Up to two accessory simple chaetae, similar to but smaller than notochaetae, inserted distally and anteriorly on neuropodial lobe (
Fig. 1C
). Ventral cirri fusiform, shorter than dorsal cirri (length 
110–270 µm
, longest on median chaetigers), arising posteroventrally on neuropodial lobe (
Fig. 1C
).
